history.content:
@6661

CS 61B is the most important class CS class you can take at Berkeley, and as a result it's recommended against that you take upper division courses without 61B unless you can self-study very effectively. You might be able to do 188 (and also Data 100) with the probability knowledge you have and good programming skills, but anything else would probably require a knowledge of data structures you won't have without 61B prior (and some of these classes will also want 61C, especially 162).

--------------------------------------------

126 is a high workload class which requires you to spend much much more time than any low divs. I would strongly suggest you take the rest of the lower div requirements and math 53 to open the door to all upper-divs. However, 188 as the easiest upper-div should be doable if you have taken 61a and 70.

I'm a freshman currently taking 61A, 16A, and 70. The courseload is very doable, so I wanted to tack on an upper div next semester. Right now, I have 126 in my proposed schedule, but was wondering about some of the other options. I'd be interested in taking 160, 161, 162, 164, 186, or 188, but it seems all of these have 61B as a prerequisite.

Which of these courses would be doable while taking 61B concurrently?
history.subject: Upper div CS courses without 61B
